  "@type": "Domain",
  "critical": false,
  "description": "Shipbuilding, marine propulsion, navigation, maritime infrastructure, and underwater engineering. Covers the engineering of vessels from dugout canoes to iron-hulled steamships, including hull construction methods, sailing rig evolution, marine engine development, harbor works, and submarine cable technology. Distinct from transport.shipping which covers water transport operations; marine covers design, construction, and maintenance of maritime systems.",
  "early_win": true,
  "early_win_note": "Dugout canoes and small sailing vessels provide coastal transport, fishing, and trade access from Year 0-5, expanding the resource base and enabling contact with other settlements",
